  "text": "The clinical relevance of irisin in humans was outside the scope of this study. This topic is disputed [CITATION_1] , and need to be further explored. Although a period of endurance [CITATION_2] or strength training [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] or both [CITATION_5] does not increase steady-state irisin levels, there may certainly be cumulative health effects of transient training-induced increases in circulating irisin.",
